  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">To study the space <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></math> of Kähler metrics, we can consider the following two geometric objects. One is the certain complexification <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">Y</mi></math> of the symplectomorphism group, and the other one is a foliation on product Kähler manifold related to the geodesic on <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">C</mi></math> . In this note we study the geometry of <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="script">Y</mi></math> and show how the properties of the associated foliation (in particular, the holomorphicity) restrict the topology of base Kähler manifold.</subfield>
